Add platform-bus NIC support for VPP via AF_XDP on NXP DPAA1 FMan.

NOTE: This file is a DESCRIPTION ONLY. The actual patching is performed
by data/scripts/patch-vpp-platform-bus.py (a Python-based patcher that
uses pattern matching instead of fragile unified diffs). The .patch file
is skipped by bin/ci-setup-vyos1x.sh — see line "vyos-1x-010-*) echo
Skipping ...".

NXP DPAA1 FMan Ethernet NICs (driver: fsl_dpa) are on the platform bus,
not PCI. At boot ALL ports (eth0-eth4) are owned by the kernel via:
  fsl_dpaa_mac  — MAC hardware control (PHY, link state)
  fsl_dpa       — Linux netdev (creates ethN)

DPDK DPAA PMD is BLOCKED for mixed kernel+VPP mode (RC#31): dpaa_bus
probe initializes ALL BMan/QMan hardware globally, killing kernel-managed
interfaces within seconds. AF_XDP is the only viable path for mixed mode
(~3.5 Gbps on 10G SFP+).

This patch enables VPP to use AF_XDP on selected DPAA1 ports when the
user configures them with 'set vpp settings interface ethX':

Modifications to src/conf_mode/vpp.py:
  1. Add 'import json' and 'import os' for DPAA helper functions
  2. Add 'fsl_dpa' to not_pci_drv list (platform bus, not PCI)
  3. Add 'fsl_dpa' to SUPPORTED_DRIVERS tuple
  4. Add DPAA1 helper functions (_dpaa_find_platform_dev, _dpaa_unbind_ifaces)
  5. CRITICAL: Replace unconditional driver='dpdk' with conditional:
     - In effective_config loop: detect original_driver via persist config,
       set driver='xdp' for fsl_dpa, driver='dpdk' for PCI NICs
     - In main config loop: same conditional + EthtoolGDrvinfo fallback
     Both paths inject default xdp_options (rx_queue_size=4096,
     tx_queue_size=4096, num_rx_queues=1) for fsl_dpa interfaces when
     CLI doesn't provide them
  6. Add _dpaa_unbind_ifaces() call before VPP start (currently a no-op
     because dpaa-ethernet.N/net/ is empty on DPAA1 — net/ lives on the
     parent fsl_dpaa_mac device, not the child fsl_dpa device)

Modifications to data/templates/vpp/startup.conf.j2:
  7. Enable af_xdp_plugin.so in plugins block
  8. Replace dpdk{} block with platform-bus-aware version (no-pci when
     only DPAA interfaces, PCI whitelist when PCI NICs present)

Modifications to python/vyos/vpp/config_verify.py:
  9. Lower main heap minimum from 1G to 256M (embedded ARM64)

Modifications to python/vyos/vpp/config_resource_checks/resource_defaults.py:
  10. Lower min_memory from 8G to 7G
  11. Lower min_cpus from 4 to 2
  12. Lower reserved_cpu_cores from 2 to 1

DPAA1 XDP MTU constraint: fsl_dpaa_mac enforces max MTU 3290 for XDP.
AF_XDP socket creation fails with EINVAL if MTU exceeds 3290. SFP+ ports
under VPP are limited to ~3304-byte max frame (3290 + 14 Ethernet header).

Port ownership lifecycle (AF_XDP — no unbind/rebind needed):
  boot               → all eth0-eth4 under kernel (fsl_dpa creates netdevs)
  set vpp ... eth3   → VPP creates AF_XDP socket on eth3 (kernel keeps netdev)
  delete vpp ... eth3→ VPP releases AF_XDP socket, kernel retains full control

Tested on NXP LS1046A Mono Gateway with VPP v25.10.0-52 AF_XDP on
eth3/eth4 (10G SFP+). Confirmed: automated AF_XDP creation via vpp.py,
LCP tap mirrors, correct MAC addresses, poll-sleep-usec 100 thermal
protection (49°C), ~5890 loops/sec.